Drawing basics - the structure of a picture, proportions, and perspective. Still lifes (combination of objects of different materials). Different drawing materials and relevant techniques. Display of works.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at supporting specialty subjects by developing the skills of visualization and picturing images in one's head as well as the skill of sketching out ideas.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students:
-	have acquired the very basics of drawing;
-	know the principles of general composition;
-	can draw according to format;
-	can convey proportions and structures;
-	know basic perspective;
-	know the application of line and surface;
-	know the principles of light-dark and light-shade.
